# Step-by-Step Instructions for Docker Setup and HDFS Operations

## 1. Navigate to the `deploy` directory
```powershell
cd deploy
```

## 2. Build the Docker image from the Dockerfile in the `deploy` directory
```powershell
docker build -t hadoop-tp3 .
```

## 3. Go back to the previous directory
```powershell
cd ..
```

## 4. Run the Docker container with the specified ports and volumes
```powershell
docker run -d -p 8088:8088 -p 9870:9870 -p 9864:9864 -v ${PWD}\data:/data -v ${PWD}\jars:/jars --rm --name=pouillieute-tp-note hadoop-tp3:latest
```

## 5. Access the container with an interactive shell
```powershell
docker exec -it pouillieute-tp-note bash
```

## 6. Create the `/relationships` directory in HDFS
```bash
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /relationships
```

## 7. Upload the `data.txt` file from the mounted volume to HDFS
```bash
hdfs dfs -put /data/relationships/data.txt /relationships/
```
